This paper is about developing an intrusion detection system using a novel concept in immunology, the Danger Theory. The paper discusses the use of Dendritic Cells (DCs) as antigen presenting cells and key to the activation of the human immune system. The DC Algorithm (DCA) is implemented using an immune inspired framework, libtissue. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
